obo:ECO_0000314  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_1799  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Literal (Fig.2): \"This indicates that Myo6 interacts with other proteins at the PSD, in addition to F-actin. In contrast, ATP treatment of Triton X-100 (TX)-permeabilized synaptosomes resulted in the release of the majority of Myo6 from the pellet fraction, suggesting that most synaptic Myo6 associates with F-actin alone (Fig. 2 C)\"\n\nThe site of this interaction is postsynaptic because MyoVI 1) binds AMPARs (Fig.6) and 2) mediates endocytosis of AMPAR (postsynaptic NT-receptor) in dendrites (Fig.7/8).\n\nMoreover, Myosins are known actin-binding proteins.. Experimental description: M&M:\nSv/wt (Myo6sv/J) mice were purchased from The Jackson Laboratory\n\nFor immunohistochemistry 1-yr-old C57/B6J mice (The Jackson Laboratory) were used.\n\nC57/B6J mouse brains or Lewis rat brain regions were homogenised and used for PSD fractionations\n\nIPs were done by extracts made from adult rat brain." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6153-3586" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2666-0758" ;
        dc:date           "2017-11-03" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1799" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

